Defines the single canonical description string of `ctx-brief`'s CLI contract, embedded as a Rust constant.

The `CONTRACT` string is the source of truth for tool-contract documentation blocks in `CLAUDE.md`/`README.md`, which are generated from `--contract` output; a `contracts` battery check compares those docs against this string and fails the build if they drift. Any change to `ctx-brief`'s CLI behavior (flags, defaults, output path, staging logic) must be reflected here or that check breaks. The text itself documents behavior owned elsewhere: two-stage `claude` invocation (gather then plan), default gather model (haiku), `--headless` semantics, and the `.context/.reports/briefs/<slug>.md` output convention — these are functional facts about the binary, not just prose, so keep this file synced with the actual CLI implementation.